text: The Embraer Emb-121 Xingu is a twin-engines light transport plane. It is both civilian and military aircraft. It's built by Embraer in Brazil. From 1982, it is used by the French Air Force and the French Navy as a training aircraft. Category:Brazilian military aircraft Category:Civil aircraft Category:French military aircraft 121
